The paper deals with the analysis of auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.DS). The paper also uses tools from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG) to derive approximation results. The focus on welfare and revenue analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfield of computational economics (cs.EC).
